<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/8(Sat.) Fukushima disaster &amp; robot (Host:Ivonne)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=205&amp;p=219#p219"><![CDATA[
9/8(Sat.) Fukushima child statue: Residents complain about radiation suit<br />&amp; 'My robot makes me feel like I haven't been forgotten' (Host : Ivonne)<br /><br />Articlle 1 ~~<br />Fukushima child statue: Residents complain about radiation suit<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-45179095">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-45179095</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussions~<br /><br />1) Why Fukushima residents reacted angrily to the statue in their city and demanded to remove it? <br /><br />2) Can you describe the Fukushima’s disaster? <br /><br />3) Fukushima disaster radiation still continues to contaminate underground water? Do you think nuclear disaster is still having an impact today? Why? <br />  <br />4) From the Chernobyl &amp; Fukushima’s disaster, do you trust the nuclear energy supply?<br /><br />5) Nuclear is potentially threatened by tsunamis, why do many countries keep pushing nuclear energy?<br /><br />6) Only days after the nuclear meltdown in Fukushima, German government previously defended nuclear energy and gradually turn off all nuclear power plants forever as well as coal in the future.  Do peoples need to fear that abandoning nuclear energy could occur another disaster?<br /><br />Article 2<br />'My robot makes me feel like I haven't been forgotten'<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-45332710">https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-45332710</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussions~<br /><br />1) What’s the Telepresence robot?<br /><br />2) How AV1 robot can help sick kids take part in lessons &amp; helps them see their friends?<br /><br />3) Do you think robot can be a pet? Will robot helps us happier instead of loneliness?<br /><br />4) Robot can do everything in the near future; does it mean we will have more time to do what we want it?<br /><br />5) Robots may soon be looking after grandma – or sharing the bed.  Please share some of the other unique impacts in the future.<br /><br />6) Robots learn to live in human society, or human learn to live as robots?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00-7:30 free talk<br />(Session 1)<br />7:30-7:35 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />7:35~ 8:15 discussion session (40 mins)<br />(Session 2)<br />8:15 ~9:00pm discussion session (45 mins)<br />9:00~9:30 free talk<br /><br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven, <br />板橋民生路二段237 號, <br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30, <br />minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Wed Sep 05, 2018 6:53 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
